transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, John. I was expecting a delivery of my prescription.

Speaker 1: I'm not sure if it's on its way or if something got dropped off.

Speaker 2: If I can get your name and zip code, I can check.

Speaker 1: Sure. Richard Barbarita, B-A-R-B-A-R-I-T-A.

Speaker 2: Zip code is 15234.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Willow Street in Pittsburgh?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: So it goes to the mailboxer.

Speaker 1: It actually says it was delivered to your mailbox this morning.

Speaker 2: This morning?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it says it was delivered at the mailbox at 10:46 a.m. local time to you.

Speaker 2: Okay. I just checked my mailbox.

Speaker 1: Do you have an apartment address?

Speaker 2: I have 4020 Willow Street, Apartment 636.

Speaker 1: Okay. 15234.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, I'll check again. I was just there like an hour ago and I didn't see it.

Speaker 2: Okay. I'm going to send you the tracking link, too, so you can see what I'm looking at.

Speaker 1: I have your email here and your first name, last name at Gmail, right?

Speaker 2: Right. With a dot in between.

Speaker 1: Okay. Gotcha. Yeah, I'll make sure that's in there.

Speaker 2: I missed reading it too quick, but, yes, I see it.

Speaker 1: So I'll go ahead and send that to you just so you have an idea of what I was looking at, too.

Speaker 2: All right. Great. I appreciate it. Thank you.

Speaker 1: No problem, sir. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
